&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THIS POST IS FIXED TERM FOR 12 MONTHS DUE TO MEET THE NEEDS OF THE SERVICE &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Linen Services Department is a part of the Facilities Directorate within the Cwm Taf Morgannwg UHB, laundering soiled linen to DHSS specifications. The post holder will be required to carry out tasks within all sections of the laundry as and when needed. The range of responsibilities will be supported and overseen by the production managers and supervisors / assistant supervisors. Supervisory staff are present in the production areas at all times of the working day to address any problem/queries with machinery or personnel. The post holder will be required to perform in set areas of work, but within an overall flexible framework. The main areas are: sorting, calendars, remat (steam finishing) towel folder, dryfold – including ironing and washing service, washer extractors and presses. Fixed Term contract&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; English and/or Welsh applicants are equally welcome to apply.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Closing date: 10th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mrs Catherine Pugh, Deputy Linen Services Manager&lt;br /&gt;Tel: 01443 443443 Ext.75489&lt;/p&gt;
